            <div type="edition" subtype="transcription" ana="b1">
                <p xml:lang="heb">דכירן לטב יהוי דכרנהון לטב כל<lb/> קהלה ק<supplied reason="lost"
                        >די</supplied>שה רביה וזעוריה דסייע<lb/> יתהון מלכיה דעלמה ואתחזקון<lb/>
                    ועבדון פסיפסה דידע שמהתון ודבניהון ודאנשי<lb/> בתיהון יכתון בספר חייה <supplied
                        reason="lost">עם</supplied>
                    <supplied reason="lost">כל</supplied><lb/> צדיקיה חברין לכל ישראל של<supplied
                        reason="lost">ום</supplied>
                    <supplied reason="lost">אמן</supplied>
                    <supplied reason="lost">סלה</supplied>
                </p>
            </div>
            <div type="translation" ana="b1">
                <p>Remembered for good be the memory for good, (including) the entire holy
                    community, the great and small ones, who were aided by the Lord of the Universe
                    and (who) donated and made the mosaic. May the One who knows their names and
                    those of their children, and of their households inscribe them in the Book of
                    Life together with the righteous, the members (friends?) of all Israel. Peace.
                    Amen, selah.</p>
            </div>
            <div type="commentary" ana="b1">
                <p>The first two lines are similar to the Jewish liturgy Yequm Purqan.</p>
            </div>
